# Frontend Development Standards

## Stack

- React 18 + TypeScript + Vite
- React Query for server state
- Zustand for client state (when needed)
- React Router v6
- Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui
- React Hook Form + Zod for forms
- i18next for internationalization scaffolding

## Component Rules

- Functional components always
- One component per file
- Props typed with TypeScript (never `any`)
- Separate logic into custom hooks
- Pure components when possible
- Co-locate tests with components

## Performance

- Initial bundle < 250KB
- Lazy loading for routes
- Core Web Vitals in green
- Optimized images

## Testing

- Vitest + React Testing Library
- Test behavior, not implementation details
- Minimum coverage: 80%
- No testing internal implementation details

## Accessibility

- WCAG AA minimum
- Semantic HTML always
- `aria-labels` where needed
- Keyboard navigation functional
- Color contrast compliant

## Package Manager

- PNPM always (not npm or yarn)
